The paper investigates the learning dynamics and emergence of compliance and enforcement of social norms in a multi-agent reinforcement learning setting. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA). Additionally, the paper uses reinforcement learning, which is a common technique in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the learning dynamics, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the emergence of group-level phenomena, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the role of punishment and incentives, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of Game Theory (cs.GT).
